lead_paragraph: Katinka Hosszu of Hungary won the women's Olympic 100 meters backstroke on Monday to claim her second gold of the Rio Games, edging out Kathleen Baker of the United States.

headline.print_headline: Hosszu Wins 100m Backstroke to Claim Second Gold
